1
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:07,000
（此为片前广告, 正片在3:02开始）

2
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Det-sen Monasnary, Tibet
德赞寺 西藏

3
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:26,500
15年前 
（这里指1980年, 因本片故事主体设定在1995年）

4
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:36,500
（西藏德赞寺是博士及其同伴杰米、维多利亚首次遭遇大智慧和雪怪的地方, 见《神秘博士》老版第五季第二集《可恶的雪人》 The Abominable Snowmen）

5
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:42,358
DISTORTED VOICE: Victoria...
维多利亚...

6
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:53,033
LAMA: What do you seek?
你在找什么？

7
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,475
It's me.
是我

8
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,517
Victoria Waterfield.
维多利亚•沃特菲尔德

9
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,594
Victoria...
维多利亚...

10
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:06,876
The Great Wheel turns.
命运之轮转动

11
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:10,919
You have been here once before.
你以前曾经到过这里

12
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,196
A long, long time ago.
很久很久以前

13
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,834
The monastery was in great danger.
那时候寺庙陷入了巨大的危机

14
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:21,919
You travelled a long, dark journey.
你走过了一段漫长而黑暗的旅程

15
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:28,997
How can one still so young
怎么可能如此年轻的一个人

16
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,475
know the depths of our darkness?
却知道我们黑暗的深处呢？

17
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,113
What has happened here?
这里发生了什么？

18
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,029
Turn back now.
现在回去吧

19
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,470
- Victoria...
-(GASPS)

20
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:41,750
My father died far away
我父亲死在一个很远的地方

21
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:45,996
- on another world.
- There are many other worlds,
- 死在另外一个世界  - 有很多其它的世界

22
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,793
other planes.
其它的平面

23
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,434
But I can hear his voice in my thoughts.
但我能在意识里听到他的声音

24
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:53,470
He's called me all this way.
他一直都在这样呼唤着我

25
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:58,390
Demons and hungry ghosts steal many shapes.
恶魔和饥饿的鬼魂会盗用许多形体

26
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:01,794
Turn away, Victoria.
掉头吧, 维多利亚

27
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:05,999
Why do you delay? Release me!
你为什么拖延？释放我吧！

28
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:10,910
I know he's here. Please tell me where to find him.
我知道他在这里. 请告诉我哪里可以找到他

29
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:15,238
A second time I ask, what do you seek?
我问第二遍, 你在找什么？

30
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:17,636
(EXCLAIMS) What have you done to him?
你把他怎么了？

31
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,274
I'm alone in the darkness.
我独自在黑暗中

32
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:24,712
Do not disturb it. It is not your father.
别惊扰它, 它不是你父亲

33
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,753
- Victoria?  - Let me through!
- 维多利亚？  - 让我过去！

34
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,029
LAMA: I cannot!
我不能

35
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:33,910
What are you hiding here? Who is it then?
你在这里藏了什么？这又是谁？

36
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:36,276
A third time I ask,
我问第三遍

37
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:38,960
what do you seek?
你在找什么？

38
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,832
I want the truth!
我在找真相！

39
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,033
You were expected.
一直在等你

40
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:54,956
My task is ended. I cannot prevent
your journey into the dark.
我的任务结束了, 我不再阻止你踏入黑暗

41
00:05:56,440 --> 00:06:00,115
The truth may light your way.
真相可能可以照亮你的路

42
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,755
Take it.
拿着

43
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,151
I've been alone,
我一直一个人

44
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,191
like you, Victoria.
跟你一样, 维多利亚

45
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,871
But together..
但是我们一起...

46
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,474
Is it you?
是你吗？

47
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,874
1 don't know.
我不知道

48
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,511
They said you were dead.
他们说你已经死了

49
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,870
But in the dreams...
但是在梦里...

50
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,630
- Victoria...  - Father?
- 维多利亚...  - 父亲吗？

51
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,472
(MOANING)

52
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,556
(FOOTSTEPS)

53
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,199
You!
是你！

54
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,794
Find me the Locus!
给我找到人偶！

55
00:06:52,000 --> 00:07:02,800
（Victoria 诞生于19世纪, 她父亲因制造时间机器而引来Daleks, 然后她和她父亲还有博士一行被 Daleks 带到 Daleks 的母星 Skaro. 当 Dalek 朝博士开枪时, 她父亲替他挡了一枪, 因此牺牲. 相关故事参见老版第四季第九集 《Dalek的邪恶》. 她父亲其实跟大智慧没有什么交集, 只是她自己一直因父亲的死而不能释怀. ）

56
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:10,000
<b>Downtime</b>

57
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,278
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING THROUGH HEADPHONES)

58
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,277
No, Gordy, I told you to play down there while I'm talking.
不, 戈迪, 我跟你说过, 我在讲电话的时候你要在下面玩

59
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:37,674
Now, off you go.
现在, 下来吧

60
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,838
Hello? Hello, Beth?
你好？你好, 贝丝

61
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,919
Look, they're still there.
看, 他们还在那儿

62
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:45,271
Those two, you know, New World weirdos, 
Chillys or whatever they're called.
这两个是什么新世界的怪人, 他们称呼为鸡仔什么的

63
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:49,278
Yes, of course, I've called the police and the council.
是的, 当然, 我已经报告给警察和地方议会了

64
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:50,993
They all think I'm crazy.
但他们觉得是我不可理喻

65
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,680
The Chillys just vanish when anyone comes,
but they're soon back.
一有人来这些鸡仔就消失了, 但很快又会回来

66
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,074
I mean, why pick me?
我是说, 为什么挑上我？

67
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:59,758
1 don't know what to do, Beth.
I have no one else to talk to.
我不知道该怎么办, 贝丝. 我找不到其它人聊这个事

68
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:02,838
BETH: Look, I'll tell you what. Why
don't you try asking your dad for help?
听着, 我告诉你怎么办, 你为什么不找你爸爸求助？

69
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,311
What? Sorry, this line's terrible.
什么？抱歉, 线路太不好了

70
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,311
My dad? God, no, I couldn't do that.
我爸爸？天呐, 不, 我不能那么干

71
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:12,080
It's been at least six years since I spoke to him.
都至少有六年我没有跟他说过话了

72
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,954
Oh, and the computer keeps crashing, so I can't work.
噢, 电脑一直宕机, 我没法工作

73
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:18,357
And that damn noise all the time,
it's like being under siege.
一直都有那个该死的噪音, 感觉像是被攻击了

74
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,630
Oh, it's disturbing. Gordy he can't stay here.
噢, 这很烦人. 戈迪他不能待在这里

75
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,878
Would you? Would you really, Beth?
你会吗？你真的会吗, 贝丝？

76
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,511
Yes. All right.
是, 好吧

77
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,551
But soon. He can't stay here.
但快点, 他不能待在这里

78
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,637
Yes, thanks, Beth. Okay, bye.
是, 谢谢, 贝丝. 好, 再见

79
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:36,000
（此角色 Kate Lethbridge-Stewart 是UNIT前负责人Gordon Lethbridge-Stewart 准将的女儿. 后来她也成了UNIT的负责人, 在《博士之日》中再次亮相, 不过不再是这个演员）

80
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:37,595
Gordy?
戈迪？

81
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,598
{(GORDY IMITATING GUN FIRING)

82
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,711
No, Gordy. Not guns. Come on, darling.
不, 戈迪, 别玩枪战了. 快来, 亲爱的

83
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:45,480
Now, come on up. Put that down.
Come on to the boat.
现在, 上这里来. 把那个放下, 快到船里来

84
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,671
I've told you before about this.
Now quickly, now.
我以前跟你说过这个. 快过来, 马上

85
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:50,474
Here we go. Up you go. Great.
来吧, 起来啰, 很好

86
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,274
Now, you go and play inside
till Beth comes, all right?
现在, 你到里面去玩, 直到贝丝过来, 好吗？

87
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,595
Off you go.
走你

88
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:57,836
KATE: Bloody Chillys!
要命的鸡仔！

89
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,435
Leave us alone!
走开！

90
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,799
Leave us alone.
走开

91
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,030
(WIND WHOOSHING)

92
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,954
(LOW GROWLING)

93
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:43,300
（Piccadilly Circus 皮卡迪利广场是伦敦一个路口的名称, 
《神秘博士》里有很多故事发生在这个地方）

94
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:08,590
MAN: (ON RADIO) The sound of the future
on 98.4 New World FM.
未来之声尽在FM98.4新世界电台

95
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:13,519
ANTHONY: (ON RADIO) And it's a Mega Morning
to all you slickers out there.
对你们所有的懒汉来说, 这是一个超级的早晨

96
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,792
You're jacked into N Treble U, the ones who share,
你现在收听的是 NTU , 一个热爱分享的电台

97
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:19,992
bringing you our daily show on National FM radio.
为你带来国家调频电台上的每日秀

98
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:23,112
I'm Anthony, and this is where
the jazzy bright day starts,
我是安东尼, 轻松明亮的一天就从这里开始

99
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:25,914
a New World coming soon, the way it always will be.
一个新世界迈步走来, 一如既往

100
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:29,709
0135-666-416.

101
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,112
We want to share that with you all.
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)
我们期望与你们所有人分享

102
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:35,437
Meantime, it can be a mean time out there, so let's...
与此同时, 它可能又是艰苦的一天...

103
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,200
<b>(New World University)</b>
（新世界大学）

104
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:46,411
(COMPUTER READING) Good morning.
Today is Thursday 14th September, 1995
<i>早上好, 今天是1995年9月14日 星期三</i>

105
00:10:46,530 --> 00:10:49,664
(COMPUTER READING) Please insert your identity code.
<i>请输入你的身份代号</i>

106
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:06,231
(COMPUTER READING) Welcome to New World.
Have the best one yet.
<i>欢迎来到新世界. 还有一个最好的</i>

107
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,594
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING THROUGH HEADPHONES)

108
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:12,280
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

109
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:16,793
Hi, welcome to New World.
How can I help you?
嗨, 欢迎来到新世界, 有什么可以帮你的？

110
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:19,355
Sarah-Jane Smith, Metropolitan magazine.
莎拉•简•史密斯, 大都市杂志社

111
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:21,915
I have an appointment
to see your vice chancellor.
我约了去见你的副校长

112
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:28,191
- I am expected. 
- At 11 o'clock. Would you like to take a seat?
- 他在等我  - 是11点, 你可以过去坐一会儿吗？

113
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:30,640
Have the best one yet.
还有一个最好的

114
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:37,399
- Miss Smith.  - Yes.
- 史密斯小姐  - 我是

115
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:39,559
Welcome to New World.
欢迎来到新世界

116
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,918
I'm so sorry if we've kept you waiting.
很抱歉让你久等了

117
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:45,229
Christopher Rice, Marketing Facilitator.
克里斯托弗·赖斯, 市场部负责人

118
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:46,395
Good morning.
早上好

119
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,989
- You brought the profiles with you, I hope. 
- Yes.
- 你把档案带过来了吧, 我期望  - 是的

120
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,270
Good. Then let's go on up.
好, 那我们上去再说吧

121
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,357
Miss Waterfield, the university's vice chancellor
沃特菲尔德小姐, 这所大学的副校长

122
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,959
would like to thank you personally.
她想亲自感谢你

123
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:05,471
I think the sum agreed was 12k,
assuming all the profiles are complete.
我想总数是一万二, 如果所有的档案都完整的话

124
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,920
Er, not quite.
呃, 不太完整

125
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:11,473
Er, Miss Smith, when we were advised of your reputation,
哦, 史密斯小姐, 当有人向我们推荐你的时候

126
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:14,149
both Miss Waterfield and I were impressed.
沃特菲尔德小姐和我都很折服

127
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:18,194
We thought, "What's a few red-tape barriers
to a journalist of this calibre?"
我们想：“对于这样一个路子宽广的记者来说, 那些繁文缛节算什么障碍？”

128
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:21,756
But you didn't tell me some of this data
was government classified.
但你们没告诉我这里某些数据是政府机密

129
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,757
(COMPUTER READING) Authorisation failure.
授权失败

130
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:30,033
You have 10 seconds to enter Stage Three security key.
你有10秒钟时间来输入第三阶段安全密钥

131
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,112
Waterfield.
沃特菲尔德

132
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:38,278
(COMPUTER READING)
You are attached to Priority Zone Z.
你已经连接到优先区域Z区

133
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,200
（他眼镜中呈现的图像很像是大智慧的三角锥/金字塔）

134
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,589
Yes!
成了！

135
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:46,713
Look, I still don't know
what New World wants these people for.
看, 我还是不知道新世界要这些人的资料做什么

136
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,917
Afraid of unearthing a scandal?
害怕发现一桩丑闻？

137
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:51,451
Half of them vanish off any records.
他们中有一半从所有记录里消失了

138
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:54,400
And what is this "London Event”
that connects them?
与他们都相关的这个“伦敦事件”又是什么？

139
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,476
What do you know?
你知道些什么？

140
00:12:57,440 --> 00:13:00,831
I've found records implying
that 25 years ago
我发现有记录显示, 在25年前

141
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:03,332
Central London was evacuated
in an industrial accident.
伦敦市中心因一起工业事故, 出现过大规模疏散的事

142
00:13:03,452 --> 00:13:05,960
（应该是指1970年前后的大智慧和雪怪入侵事件, 见第五季第二季《恐惧之网》, 不过该事件的具体时间不详）

143
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:09,316
They say it lasted three months.
There are no extant reports.
他们说这事持续了三个月, 但目前没有见到有报告保存下来

144
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:12,159
No one even remembers. Well, how can that happen?
也没有人记得. 你说, 这怎么可能呢？

145
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:16,394
The London Event was a wasted opportunity.
伦敦事件是一次被浪费掉的契机

146
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:21,080
The world missed out on an interface
with a higher plane of existence.
这个世界错过了一个与更高层面存在打交道的接口

147
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,349
It's no big deal.
这没什么要紧

148
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:26,193
There will be other chances.
还会有其它机会的

149
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:29,036
It was totally misunderstood.
这被完全误解了

150
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:32,357
We all stumbled about
in the unknowing darkness.
我们都还困在莫名的黑暗中

151
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:35,040
New World seeks to
light the first candle.
新世界致力于点亮第一根蜡烛

152
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,635
Oh, come on.
噢, 得了

153
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:39,070
New World's more than just
a New Age Sunday School.
新世界不仅仅是一所新时代的主日学校

154
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,873
You've got fingers in more pies
than Robert Maxwell.
你们的手指比罗伯特·马克斯维尔还多

155
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:46,359
I'm afraid we've wasted your time, Miss Smith.
恐怕我们耽误你的时间了, 史密斯小姐

156
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:48,869
You already knew.
你已经知道了

157
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:50,869
New World has the solution.
新世界找到解决方案了

158
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,479
That's our motto.
这是我们的座右铭

159
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,918
Our programme.
我们的课程

160
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,514
If you've got such high-flying sources,
why employ me?
如果里面有如此高的消息来源, 为什么还雇我？

161
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,596
There is one name
missing from your list.
你的清单里少了一个名字

162
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:06,078
Not to my knowledge.
据我所知没有

163
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:08,635
But much to ours.
但对我们很重要

164
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,275
Lethbridge-Stewart.
利斯布里奇-斯图尔特. 

165
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:15,031
What do they want old Stewpot for?
他们找这个老斯图做什么？

166
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:22,718
United Nations Intelligence Task-force
is a paramilitary espionage squad.
UNIT（联合国情报部门行动组）是一个准军事间谍小组

167
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:25,710
It's the old MI5 story.
这是老旧的军情五处类的故事

168
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:30,232
Everyone knows it's there, but no
one knows what its real agenda is.
每个人都知道它的存在, 但没有人清楚它的真正目标是什么

169
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,432
Even those who work for it.
即使是那些为他工作的人

170
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:39,076
Alistair Gordon Lethbridge-Stewart figures
largely in its setting up in the '70s.
在它70年代的成立过程中, Listair Gordon Lethbridge-Stewart 扮演了很重要的角色

171
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:42,636
By then, he's a brigadier
with a remarkable active service record.
那时, 他是一个准将, 有着出色的服役记录

172
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:45,318
And then he vanishes.
然后他就消失了

173
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:49,278
You must have known him
during your time with UNIT.
你肯定认识他, 那段时间你也在UNIT

174
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,913
Sorry to disappoint you,
but I'm just a journalist.
让你们失望了, 我只是一个记者

175
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,913
With no official records
of Lethbridge-Stewart,
由于没有关于 Lethbrige-Stewart 的官方记录

176
00:14:57,680 --> 00:15:00,194
one could easily imagine he was dead.
其他人就会很轻易地认为他已经死了

177
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:02,199
UNIT looks after its own.
UNIT 会保护他们自己人

178
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:04,677
What's this brigadier supposed to have done?
你们觉得这个准将都做了什么？

179
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:07,152
He has committed a great crime.
他犯了一项巨大的罪行

180
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:10,400
But there are other ways of seeking him.
但还是有其它方法找到他

181
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:12,989
(SPHERE BEEPING)

182
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:14,876
(BANG)

183
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,719
(PULSATING)

184
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:32,029
(SPHERE BEEPING AND PULSATING)

185
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,673
Someone in the secure system.
有人进入了安全系统

186
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:35,598
- What's happening?
- Daniel Hinton.
- 怎么回事？ - 是丹尼尔·辛顿

187
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:40,032
- That devious little...
- I don't want him hurt, Christopher.
- 那个狡猾的小...  - 我不想他受伤, 克里斯托弗

188
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:41,275
Of course.
当然

189
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,039
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING THROUGH HEADPHONES)

190
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:50,436
MAN: (ON RADIO) And that's the
Acoustic Hoods here at Top o'the Clock.

191
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:52,233
You're jacked into N Treble U
你收听的是 NTU 电台

192
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:54,636
from New World,
the people with the solution,
由有解决方案的人 - 新世界为你带来

193
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:56,671
and we ain't talking watered down here.
我们的节目不兑水

194
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:59,314
If you can't get your
head round life, no hassle.
如果你不能从生活中抬起头来, 没有问题

195
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:02,478
There's over 300 different courses
here at New World.
新世界有300多种不同的课程

196
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,671
So there's got to be a right one for you,
hasn't there?
所以总有一款适合你, 是吧？

197
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:07,394
Give us a call. 0135-66...
给我们来电话, 0135-66...

198
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,550
There he is!
他在那儿！

199
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,996
(SPHERE BEEPING AND PULSATING)

200
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:37,672
What is New World University?
新世界大学是什么？

201
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:40,829
You don't have lectures.
You don't even have tutors.
你们没有讲座, 你们连老师都没有

202
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:44,872
All the tuition is conducted by the mainframe,
所有的授课都是由靠电脑主机来进行

203
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,071
a personalised syllabus for every student.
为每个学生提供个性化的教学大纲

204
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:49,631
Since when did computers get personal?
电脑什么时候开始有个性了？

205
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:52,236
(BEEPING AND PULSATING)

206
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:03,393
Come on, what are the Chillys really for?
说说, 鸡仔真正是干什么的

207
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:05,318
A sort of a fascist hippy cult?
一种法西斯嬉皮士邪教？

208
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:10,551
The wicked world is full of lost children,
the aimless, the lonely.
这个邪恶的世界里到处都是失落的孩子, 漫无目的, 孤独无助

209
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:14,875
We follow the Det-sen disciplines
which we share with our Chancellor.
我们遵循德赞信条, 这点我们与校长是一致的

210
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:17,950
We really do care.
我们真的在意

211
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:21,353
Well, where is he then? Why can't I see him?
那, 他在哪儿？我怎么见不到他？

212
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:23,232
The Chancellor sees no one.
校长不见任何人

213
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:26,959
He has taken the Path of Truth.
他已经走上了真理之路

214
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,553
Victoria Waterfield.
维多利亚•沃特菲尔德

215
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,870
That's you on the list, isn't it?
At the London Event?
在名单上的是你, 对不？伦敦事件的时候

216
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:35,633
Oh, you must have been really young.
噢, 你那时一定很年轻

217
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:39,196
Considering I was born over 140 years ago...
考虑到我是140多年前出生的...

218
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:42,754
Peanuts, I used to know someone who...
花生, 我以前认识一个能够...

219
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:43,915
Oh, never mind.
噢, 算了

220
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:47,837
Oh, sorry, I mean, no,
you don't look a day over...
哦, 抱歉, 我是说, 你看起来一天也没有超过（结束）...

221
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:50,952
I don't feel a day over. (LAUGHING)
我从没感觉到一天结束(?)

222
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:56,556
(COMPUTER READING ON LOOP)
Find the Locus.
找到人偶

223
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,159
(WHIMPERS)

224
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:08,269
We all have pain to face, Sarah,
我们都有痛苦要面对, 莎拉

225
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,800
but the revelation will be soon.
但启示很快就会出现

226
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:16,798
(COMPUTER READING ON LOOP)

227
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,550
(SPHERE BEEPING AND PULSATING)

228
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:24,280
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING
THROUGH HEADPHONES)

229
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,470
Come on, Daniel.
来吧, 丹尼尔

230
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:32,478
Nothing to be afraid of.
没什么可害怕的

231
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,879
We're here to help you.
我们是来帮你的

232
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:37,394
You've been chosen.
你被选中了

233
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,670
It's a sham!
这是假象！

234
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:48,279
The whole thing!
这整件事！

235
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:49,879
It'll get you all!
它会抓到你们所有人！

236
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,676
It already has you, Daniel.
它已经抓到你了, 丹尼尔

237
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,435
Go on, then.
继续啊

238
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,557
There's no escape, not even that way.
你没法逃掉了, 就是那边也不行

239
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:04,153
-(DANIEL SCREAMING)
-(WHISPERING) Daniel!
丹尼尔！

240
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:13,715
-(WIND HOWLING)
-(CROWD CHATTERING)

241
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,355
MAN: Ball!
球！

242
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:50,915
Sir? Please, sir?
长官？打扰了, 长官

243
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:54,195
Hinton? What are you doing here?
辛顿？你在这里做什么？

244
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:56,709
Hinton, D.A., sir. School House 91.
辛顿, 地方检察官, 长官. 布伦登学校91届

245
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:04,353
It must be a good three years
since you got yourself expelled.
你被开除后这三年过得肯定很不错

246
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:07,791
Yes, sir, but I need to talk to you now.
Sir, It's important.
是的, 长官, 但我现在需要和你谈谈. 长官, 很重要的事

247
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,992
Frankly, Hinton, I don't know
how you could throw it all away.
坦白说, 辛顿, 我不知道你怎么能把一切都扔掉

248
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:15,950
You excel at maths and computer work...
你擅长数学和计算机工作..

249
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,833
The headmaster says I'm "a disruptive influence”.
校长说我有“破坏性的影响”

250
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:20,189
It wasn't deliberate, sir.
这不是故意的, 长官

251
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:24,834
No more than losing your CCF kit
or skiving off games.

252
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:27,120
(SIGHS) This occult nonsense.
这太荒诞了

253
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,475
(SIGHS) This occult nonsense.
这太荒诞了

254
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:32,353
Dabbling with black magic
is a dangerous business.
玩弄黑魔法是件危险的事

255
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:35,518
It was a séance, sir.
Not magic, or drugs.
那是个集会, 长官. 没有魔法, 没有磕药

256
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:38,234
- No?  - I've done it loads of times.
- 不是？ - 我已经做过好多次了

257
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,754
I suppose it's a gift.
我想这是种天份

258
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:42,516
You have no idea
what you're dealing with.
你完全不知道你在对付什么

259
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:44,756
No, sir. Not natural, is it?
不知道, 长官. 超自然的东西, 对不？

260
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:49,472
Do you have a family, sir?
你有家庭吗, 长官？

261
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,516
You realise we're under surveillance.
你该意识到我们被监视了吧

262
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:07,472
Tsk. Wretched boy.
唉, 可怜的男孩

263
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:25,711
(DISTORTED) Where is the Locus?
人偶在哪儿？

264
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:28,309
Who are you?
你是谁？

265
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:33,318
(MONSTER GROWLING)

266
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:42,315
(STATIC)

267
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,590
ANSWERING MACHINE: This is 
Alistair Lethbridge-Stewart at Brendon.
这里是布伦登的Alistair Lethbridge-Stewart家

268
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,791
Leave your name, number
and message after the tone,
在嘀的一声后, 留下你的名字、电话和留言

269
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:48,593
and I'll call you back as soon as possible.
我会尽快给你打回去的

270
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:49,915
(ANSWERING MACHINE CLICKS)

271
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:53,795
WOMAN: Oh, hello, er, Brigadier?
This is the headmaster's secretary.
噢, 你好, 准将. 这里是校长秘书处

272
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:56,036
We were concerned that you missed the meeting
我们对你没来参加聚会的事颇为关切

273
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,992
about your retirement party this morning.
今早是你的退休欢送会

274
00:21:59,080 --> 00:22:02,232
We've also had several rather
strange phone enquiries about you.
我们还接到几个奇怪的电话, 都是在问你的问题

275
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:05,079
Could you get in touch ASAP? Thank you.
你能尽快与我们联系吗, 谢谢

276
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:06,520
(ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS)

277
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:08,278
I thought I was in Cromer.
我以为我在克罗默

278
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:16,232
-(STATIC STOPS)
-(CROWD CHATTERING)

279
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,355
Tuesday?
星期二了？

280
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:48,471
(ANSWERING MACHINE REWINDING)

281
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,029
(ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS)

282
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:16,232
KATE: Look, erm, it's me, Dad.
是这样, 嗯, 是我, 爸爸

283
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:18,476
- I'm sorry, I know it's been a long time.
- Kate!
- 我很抱歉, 我知道太长时间了  - 凯特！

284
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:21,274
This'll be a shock and all that...
but can I see you?
这很突然而且又...但我能见你吗？

285
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,115
Soon please, Dad.
尽快好吗, 爸爸

286
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:28,159
Sorry. It's, erm, 0585-226-904.
抱歉, 我的号码是0585-226-904

287
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:31,510
Erm, thanks. (BEEPS)
嗯, 谢谢

288
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:35,235
(ANSWERING MACHINE)
Saturday, 3:44 p.m.
星期六, 下午 3:44

289
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:39,154
Stupid machine.
Can't have been asleep that long.
愚蠢的机器. 我不可能睡了那么久

290
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:42,790
(CROWD CHATTERING)

291
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,874
(BEEPS)

292
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:58,837
MALE VOICE:
Greyhound is asked to call Trap Six.
请求灰狗联系陷阱六号
